docs.name: Agricultural Production Index - Thailand
docs.description: Agricultural Production Index for Thailand. Source: FAOSTAT. The FAO indices of agricultural production show the relative level of the aggregate volume of agricultural production for each year in comparison with the base period 1999-2001. They are based on the sum of price-weighted quantities of different agricultural commodities produced after deductions of quantities used as seed and feed weighted in a similar manner. The resulting aggregate represents, therefore, disposable production for any use except as seed and feed. For more information, see http://faostat.fao.org/site/612/default.aspx#ancor>http://faostat.fao.org/site/612/default.aspx#ancor
